events.name: Mobile Sites Certification - Study Jam by GDG Zamboanga

venue.name: Institute of Computer Studies, Western Mindanao State University

events.description:
• What we'll do
Mobile Sites Certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate understanding in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

Our Facilitators will go through the concepts, then participants will take the FREE Certification Exam from Google. Participants who got 85% or higher rate from the exam will receive a printable Google Certificate and be a certified mobile sites professional. • What to bring
Laptop (make sure you have enough battery life)
Personal Internet Connection (if any)

• Important to know
This event is FREE but slots are limited. Only confirmed participants (RSVPed Yes) can be accommodated. Make sure that your FULL NAME on your profile is correct.

events.name: International Women's Day (IWD) - Women Techmakers Zamboanga 2018
events.description:
Women Techmakers is Google's global program and brand for women in technology. Women Techmakers program provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology.

GDG Zamboanga is once again organizing Women Techmakers Zamboanga 2018 this April 22 at the TESDA ARMM Language Skills Institute located at Veterans Avenue in Zamboanga City.

Women Techmakers Zamboanga is designed to showcase the work of women in the various industry (technology, education, health, and etc.) by providing a platform to celebrate their talents and spotlight role models. Through this program, GDG Zamboanga aims to increase women visibility in tech. Women Techmakers is also a platform in recognizing women who made a significant contribution to the community and a place to advance, grow and celebrate women in tech.

Women Techmakers Zamboanga 2018 is building a new horizon by featuring Mobile Site Certification where participants can take the certification exam and be certified by Google.

So what are you waiting for?
Join #WTMZamboanga 2018! But, you have to register first and wait for our confirmation!

REGISTRATION LINK: http://bit.ly/wtmzambo18
PROGRAMME: http://bit.ly/WTMZambo18Programme

IMPORTANT REMINDERS:

This event is FREE but slots are limited. Only confirmed participants can be accommodated. Make sure that your FULL NAME on your profile is correct. We encourage you to BYOD (bring your own device). AM and PM snacks will be provided

events.name: Google Assistant : Build Actions for your Community
events.description:
Registration Link: https://goo.gl/eevf4P

Actions on Google and Google Assistant are one of the major Google technical areas and we want to invite the whole developer community to learn about creating Actions for the Google Assistant.

“Build Actions for Your Community” is an open and modular event series designed by Google and offered to community organizers worldwide. We offer opportunities to developers attending our events to learn how to build Actions for the Google Assistant that are useful to the community - whether it's a professional network, interest group, or our hometown. This way, we can build something in an area that we care about or are interested in.

Actions on Google let you build for the Google Assistant. Your integrations can help you engage users through Google Home, Android & iOS phones, Wear OS, Android TV, and Smart Displays and more in the future.

This event is FREE but slots are limited. Only confirmed participants will be accommodated on the day of the event.

Like our Facebook Page (https://www.facebook.com/gdgzambo) for updates about the event.

events.name: DevFest Zamboanga Peninsula 2018
events.description:
GDG DevFest 2018 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, all-day hack-a-thons, codelabs, and more.

DevFest Zamboanga Peninsula 2018 is a two-day conference anchored on the theme "Digital Well-being". Google values the total experience of its users and that's includes our over-all health while engaging with its technologies. At DevFest we will be incorporating topics that would help users be mindful while engaging in the digital world aside from the technical ones.

The first day (December 3) of DevFest will be Codelabs Session with three different topics in two different venues.

Codelabs 1:
"Building User Interfaces and Single-page Apps using Vue.js"

Venue: DICT MC1 Office
Time: 8am to 5pm

Codelabs 2:
"Android + Firebase"

Venue: Sangguniang Panlungsod
Time: 8am to 12nn

Codelabs 3:
"Google Cloud Vision API"

Venue: Sangguniang Panlungsod
Time: 1pm to 5pm

The second day of DevFest will be Speakers Session which will be held at Dr. Juanito Bruno Gymnasium, Western Mindanao State University.
